<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Legs with femora fusiform; tibiae with pair of distal black brownish spines; tarsomere 
<number box="[1170,1212,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
rounded, with wide pulvillae; 
<number box="[263,277,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="1.0">1</number>
longer than 
<number box="[418,463,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
, which are progressively longer; 
<number box="[835,849,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="5.0">5</number>
clavate, with separate claws.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="187" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
