<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,335,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is in honour of Dr. Charles L. 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1047,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamy">Bellamy</taxonomicName>
, who very kindly helped us and encouraged us in the study of 
<taxonomicName box="[487,621,367,391]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Buprestidae</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[658,730,367,391]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="187" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</emphasis>
Each species has a distinctive pronotal shape and colour pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1210,404,428]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStart-1="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Figs. 
<number box="[1149,1210,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="8.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="4.0">4–13</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1362,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[1231,1362,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,161,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="1.0">1</number>
–4
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[210,224,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">8</figureCitation>
) resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[365,491,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocularis">
<emphasis box="[365,491,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. ocularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[509,591,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[606,621,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">9</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[646,760,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suarezi">
<emphasis box="[646,760,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. suarezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[778,860,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[875,902,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">11</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1126,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeclarus">
<emphasis box="[972,1126,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. praeclarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1145,1229,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Fig. 
<number box="[1200,1229,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) in the two black transverse vittae of the apical half of the elytra. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[825,954,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[825,954,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1264,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeclarus">
<emphasis box="[1110,1264,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. praeclarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the convex frons and pronotum lacking a longitudinal groove. In 
<taxonomicName box="[799,958,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeclarus">
<emphasis box="[799,958,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. praeclarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the frons is strongly depressed and the pronotum has a longitudinal median groove, which extends from the anterior margin without reaching the middle. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,280,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[151,280,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pronotum with anterior margin slightly sinuate, with punctures moderately fine, very sparse; in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[287,376,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[397,426,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">10</figureCitation>
) the anterior margin is strongly sinuate with prominent subrectangular projection. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName box="[304,431,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[304,431,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger than 
<taxonomicName box="[590,733,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis box="[590,733,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the space between the punctures less than the diameter of each puncture; by contrast, 
<taxonomicName box="[461,605,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis box="[461,605,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotum with weak and sparse punctures; the space between the punctures at least, 
<number box="[363,430,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">
3 to 
<date box="[416,430,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">4</date>
</number>
x the diameter of a puncture. 
<taxonomicName box="[775,903,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[775,903,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1187,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocularis">
<emphasis box="[1063,1187,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. ocularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1357,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suarezi">
<emphasis box="[1244,1357,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. suarezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the colour pattern of the elytra and pronotum; 
<taxonomicName box="[638,766,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[638,766,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a broad black vitta on elytral suture and the pronotum entirely black, like 
<emphasis box="[366,674,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName box="[366,521,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeclarus">A. praeclarus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[532,674,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">A. pygmaeus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[728,862,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valverdei">
<emphasis box="[728,862,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. valverdei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[877,959,799,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[167,1411,198,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[167,1411,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Habitus: 8, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 9, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 10, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 11, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962); 12, A. valverdei (Cobos, 1962); 13, A. praeclarus (Perroud, 1853). Scale bar: 2 mm. (Photo 12, by Mercedes P. García, MNCN)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Fig. 
<number box="[929,959,799,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName box="[1049,1171,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocularis">
<emphasis box="[1049,1171,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. ocularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1225,1336,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suarezi">
<emphasis box="[1225,1336,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. suarezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the black vitta of the elytral suture progressively narrowed, and the pronotum has the lateral margins red. 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1436,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the posterior angles pointed and oblique, and a moderate elevation between the eyes, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1389,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocularis">
<emphasis box="[1266,1389,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. ocularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,261,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suarezi">
<emphasis box="[151,261,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. suarezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have moderate depression between the eyes. 
<taxonomicName box="[768,895,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[768,895,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1175,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valverdei">
<emphasis box="[1042,1175,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. valverdei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the size (
<taxonomicName box="[1316,1436,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamy">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger) and shape of the pronotum; 
<taxonomicName box="[585,715,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[585,715,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotum widest behind the middle (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1317,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,202,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1386,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. 1 – 3. Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal view (scale bar: 1 mm); 2, frontal view of head (scale bar: 0,5 mm); 3, ventral view of antennae (scale bar: 0,25 mm). 4 – 7. Pronotum: 4, Agrilozodes bellamyi Portela &amp; Mermudes sp. nov., holotype male; 5, A. ocularis (Kerremans, 1903); 6, A. pygmaeus (Kerremans, 1897); 7, A. suarezi (Cobos, 1962). Scale bar: 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215636/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">
Figs. 
<number box="[1301,1317,943,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valverdei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. valverdei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the opposite; 
<taxonomicName box="[457,591,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valverdei">
<emphasis box="[457,591,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. valverdei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[800,927,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilozodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[800,927,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="187">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the two parallel black vittae at the middle of elytra.
</paragraph>
